v9.0.1 - Metadata null-clear fix:

Fixes artwork URL and all metadata string/numeric fields not being cleared when
the server sends an explicit null. Music Assistant sends artwork_url: null when
transitioning to an artless track, and clears all fields via cleared_update()
when playback stops. The SDK was using ?? merge semantics which treated explicit
null identically to absent — silently retaining the previous value in both cases.

Extended the existing Optional&lt;T&gt; pattern from the progress field to all
ServerMetadata fields (title, artist, album_artist, album, artwork_url, year,
track, timestamp). Absent = keep existing, explicit null = clear. This matches
aiosendspin's UndefinedField on every metadata field and fixes the three-layer
artwork persistence bug observed in the Windows client.

