v9.0.0 - Full Role Coverage and Spec Conformance:

This release completes every Sendspin protocol role and closes a cross-SDK
conformance audit. All six roles are now implemented: player, controller,
metadata, artwork, color, and visualizer.

NEW ROLES AND FEATURES:
- Color role (color@v1): receives the audio-derived palette on GroupState.Colors
  with a ColorChanged event (RgbColor, spec delta semantics).
- Visualizer role (visualizer@v1): six feature types (loudness, f_peak, spectrum,
  beat, peak, pitch) via VisualizationReceived; opt-in. Mirrors the aiosendspin
  reference, which is ahead of the formal spec and may still evolve.
- Artwork role completed: 1-4 independent channels, channel/timestamp-aware
  events, stream/request-format, source "none".
- Controller role completed: GroupState.SupportedCommands, SetMuteAsync.
- Player timing capabilities: required_lead_time_ms, min_buffer_ms, the
  set_static_delay command, and IStaticDelayStore for cross-restart persistence.
- repeat/shuffle now read from the controller state object; mac_address in
  device_info; perceptual volume curve; client/state error/synchronized on
  pipeline error/recovery; player/artwork/visualizer stream/request-format emit;
  delta client/state; external_source enter/exit API.

BREAKING CHANGES:
- Removed the non-spec client/sync_offset message and the SyncOffsetApplied
  event / SyncOffsetEventArgs. Use the server/command set_static_delay path.
- ArtworkReceived is now EventHandler&lt;ArtworkReceivedEventArgs&gt; and
  ArtworkCleared is EventHandler&lt;ArtworkClearedEventArgs&gt; (both carry the
  channel and timestamp).
- ClientCapabilities.ArtworkFormats / ArtworkMaxSize removed in favor of
  ArtworkChannels (1-4 per-channel specs).
- StreamRequestFormatMessage reshaped to the spec payload envelope.
- repeat/shuffle removed from the TrackMetadata model (now on GroupState).
- The default client/goodbye reason changed from "user_request" to "restart"
  so an unexplained disconnect is reconnectable; pass an explicit reason to
  opt out.

